---
interface Props {
  context?: "article" | "architecture";
  lang?: "fr" | "en";
}

const { context = "article", lang = "fr" } = Astro.props;

const copy = {
  fr: {
    ariaLabel:
      "Schéma : avant, Cloudflare relayait le trafic public directement vers le serveur via une règle de pare-feu ouvrant les ports 80 et 443 ; après, le serveur initie lui-même une connexion sortante vers Cloudflare (tunnel cloudflared), qui achemine le trafic public à travers cette connexion déjà établie, sans aucun port ouvert. Une fois arrivé sur le serveur, le trafic est relayé par le proxy inverse vers les services internes, peu importe le chemin emprunté.",
    cloudflare: "Cloudflare",
    cloudflareSub: "(trafic public)",
    serveur: "serveur",
    serveurSub: "(cloudflared)",
    proxy: "proxy inverse",
    proxySub: "(TLS, routage)",
    avant: "avant · pare-feu (80/443 ouverts)",
    apres: "après · tunnel sortant",
    services1: "services",
    services2: "internes",
  },
  en: {
    ariaLabel:
      "Diagram: before, Cloudflare relayed public traffic straight to the server through a firewall rule opening ports 80 and 443; after, the server itself initiates an outbound connection to Cloudflare (cloudflared tunnel), which routes public traffic through that already-established connection, with no port open at all. Once it reaches the server, traffic is relayed by the reverse proxy to internal services either way.",
    cloudflare: "Cloudflare",
    cloudflareSub: "(public traffic)",
    serveur: "server",
    serveurSub: "(cloudflared)",
    proxy: "reverse proxy",
    proxySub: "(TLS, routing)",
    avant: "before · firewall (80/443 open)",
    apres: "after · outbound tunnel",
    services1: "internal",
    services2: "services",
  },
} as const;

const t = copy[lang];
---

<figure class="tunnel-diagram">
  <div class="diagram-wrap">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 760 260" role="img" aria-label={t.ariaLabel}>
      <defs>
        <marker id="ct-arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse">
          <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="var(--text-faint)" />
        </marker>
        <marker id="ct-arrow-live" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse">
          <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="var(--accent-live)" />
        </marker>
      </defs>

      <!-- Cloudflare -->
      <ellipse cx="70" cy="130" rx="65" ry="32" fill="var(--panel)" stroke="var(--panel-border)" />
      <text x="70" y="126" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="12" fill="var(--text)">{t.cloudflare}</text>
      <text x="70" y="142" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="10.5" fill="var(--text-faint)">{t.cloudflareSub}</text>

      <!-- serveur (cloudflared) -->
      <rect x="260" y="98" width="150" height="64" rx="6" fill="var(--panel)" stroke="var(--panel-border)" stroke-width="1.5" />
      <text x="335" y="124" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-display)" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="var(--text)">{t.serveur}</text>
      <text x="335" y="141" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="10.5" fill="var(--text-faint)">{t.serveurSub}</text>

      <!-- proxy inverse -->
      <rect x="470" y="98" width="150" height="64" rx="6" fill="var(--panel)" stroke="var(--panel-border)" stroke-width="1.5" />
      <text x="545" y="124" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-display)" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="var(--text)">{t.proxy}</text>
      <text x="545" y="141" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="10.5" fill="var(--text-faint)">{t.proxySub}</text>

      <!-- avant : pare-feu entrant -->
      <path d="M136,113 L258,113" fill="none" stroke="var(--text-faint)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#ct-arrow)" />
      <text x="197" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="11" fill="var(--text-faint)">{t.avant}</text>

      <!-- après : tunnel sortant, initié par le serveur -->
      <path d="M258,150 L136,150" fill="none" stroke="var(--accent-live)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="5 4" marker-end="url(#ct-arrow-live)" />
      <text x="197" y="177" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="11" fill="var(--accent-live)">{t.apres}</text>

      <!-- serveur -> proxy inverse -> services internes (inchangé avant/après) -->
      <path d="M412,130 L468,130" fill="none" stroke="var(--text-faint)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#ct-arrow)" />
      <path d="M622,130 L700,130" fill="none" stroke="var(--text-faint)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#ct-arrow)" />
      <text x="700" y="112" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="11" fill="var(--text-faint)">{t.services1}</text>
      <text x="700" y="126" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="11" fill="var(--text-faint)">{t.services2}</text>
    </svg>
  </div>
  <figcaption>
    {
      context === "architecture" ? (
        lang === "en" ? (
          <>
            Detail of the <a href="/inventaire/proxy-inverse/">reverse proxy</a> role: public traffic used to go
            through a firewall rule opening ports 80/443, before switching to a Cloudflare tunnel initiated by the
            server itself — no more inbound port to maintain. Once it arrives, traffic is relayed as before to
            internal services. See the article:{" "}
            <a href="/blog/retirer-pare-feu-tunnel-cloudflare/">zero firewall, one tunnel</a>.
          </>
        ) : (
          <>
            Détail du rôle <a href="/inventaire/proxy-inverse/">proxy inverse</a> : le trafic public passait par une
            règle de pare-feu ouvrant les ports 80/443, avant de basculer sur un tunnel Cloudflare initié par le
            serveur lui-même — plus aucun port entrant à maintenir. Une fois arrivé, le trafic est relayé comme avant
            vers les services internes. Voir l'article :{" "}
            <a href="/blog/retirer-pare-feu-tunnel-cloudflare/">zéro pare-feu, un tunnel</a>.
          </>
        )
      ) : lang === "en" ? (
        <>
          Before/after: from a firewall rule opening 80/443 to an outbound tunnel initiated by the server. See the{" "}
          <a href="/architecture/">architecture overview</a>.
        </>
      ) : (
        <>
          Avant/après : d'une règle de pare-feu ouvrant 80/443 à un tunnel sortant initié par le serveur. Voir la{" "}
          <a href="/architecture/">vue d'ensemble de l'architecture</a>.
        </>
      )
    }
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .tunnel-diagram {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .diagram-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--bg);
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  svg {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    min-width: 560px;
    height: auto;
  }

  figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    max-width: var(--measure);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-faint);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  figcaption a {
    color: var(--accent-live);
  }
</style>
